  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-01-27",
    "date": "2009-02-21T18:13:07Z",
    "text": "Citizen Involvement in Campaigns Act of 2009- Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow: (1) a $200 tax credit ($400 for joint returns) for contributions to a candidate for federal elective public office or to the national committee of a national political party; and (2) a tax deduction (available to taxpayers who do not itemize deductions) for such political contributions up to $600 ($1,200 for joint returns)."
  },
